    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1864-03-09T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1864-03-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="144" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d144">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Judd</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 66.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1864-03-09">
                            <hi rend="italic">March</hi> 9, 1864</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> I have the honor to acknowledge the
                            receipt of your despatch of the 11th of February, No. 56, and I give you
                            my sincere thanks for the exposition of the political and military
                            movements of the allies in the war against Denmark. Information from
                            London of a date somewhat later than yours induces a belief that some
                            settlement of the controversy is at hand. Nevertheless, this information
                            comes through channels that are not altogether reliable. The British
                            people desire a settlement so earnestly that their opinions and even
                            their facts take a coloring from their wishes.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM EL SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Norman B. Judd</hi>, Esq., &amp;<hi rend="italic">c</hi>., &amp;<hi rend="italic">c</hi>., &amp;<hi rend="italic">c</hi>.<hi rend="italic">, Berlin.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
